###Background
The Siege of Ladysmith was a protracted engagement in the Second Boer War. 
__It took place between 30 October 1899 and 28 February 1900 at Ladysmith, Natal__.

British commander Lieutenant General Sir George White made Ladysmith his center of operations for the protection of Natal against the Boer forces. Starting on 29 October 1899 a number of short lived battles were fought for control of the town, but after suffering heavy casualties the British forces retreated to Ladysmith and the Boer forces did not make use of the opportunity to follow up the attack and take control of the town.
